{"type":"standard","title":"South Pole","displaytitle":"<span lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><span class=\"mw-page-title-main\">South Pole</span></span>","namespace":{"id":0,"text":""},"wikibase_item":"Q933","titles":{"canonical":"South_Pole","normalized":"South Pole","display":"<span lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><span class=\"mw-page-title-main\">South Pole</span></span>"},"pageid":20611127,"thumbnail":{"source":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/59/Pole-south.gif","width":330,"height":330},"originalimage":{"source":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/59/Pole-south.gif","width":330,"height":330},"lang":"en","dir":"ltr","revision":"1349060575","tid":"3861edc2-38df-11f1-81e0-aa63a1d7eb47","timestamp":"2026-04-15T15:24:40Z","description":"Southernmost point on Earth","description_source":"local","content_urls":{"desktop":{"page":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Pole","revisions":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Pole?action=history","edit":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Pole?action=edit","talk":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Talk:South_Pole"},"mobile":{"page":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Pole","revisions":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:History/South_Pole","edit":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Pole?action=edit","talk":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Talk:South_Pole"}},"extract":"The South Pole, also known as the Geographic South Pole or Terrestrial South Pole, is the point in the Southern Hemisphere where the Earth's axis of rotation meets its surface. It is called the True South Pole to distinguish from the south magnetic pole.","extract_html":"<p>The <b>South Pole</b>, also known as the <b>Geographic South Pole</b> or <b>Terrestrial South Pole</b>, is the point in the Southern Hemisphere where the Earth's axis of rotation meets its surface. It is called the <b>True South Pole</b> to distinguish from the south magnetic pole.</p>"}